# ============================================================
# Doc_V2/.gitignore
# Keeps customer-specific drafts and internal-only artifacts
# OFF the public repo while everything else syncs to mobile.
# ============================================================

# ─── Customer-specific (per-customer engagement records) ───
# Per-customer folders contain pricing, PoC drafts, prospect profiles.
# Index file mentions customer names too. Keep entire customer-accounts/ folder local-only.
10-customer-success/customer-accounts/

# Customer-specific files anywhere (catch-all pattern)
**/SANPRAS-*
**/NOVEX-*

# ─── Internal-only sales handlers ───
# The sales-team Q&A appendix doc and discount thresholds
# Stay private. Generic SALES-PLAYBOOK is fine to publish.
**/*-SALES.md
**/*-SALES.html
**/*-SALES.pdf

# ─── Rendered output (regenerate from source) ───
# HTML and PDF bloat git history; rebuild via _scripts/render-docs.mjs
*.html
*.pdf
# Exception: from-Web bundle PDFs ARE canonical (not regeneratable) — keep them
!from*Web/**/*.pdf
# Exception: hero SVG artwork PDF previews if any
!_assets/**/*.pdf

# ─── Build/scratch ───
_scratch/
DRAFT-*.md
_scripts/temp/
_scripts/node_modules/

# ─── Web-bundle artifacts that are huge / archival ───
# The 6.9MB chat-artifacts zip bloats history; keep the PDFs but not the zip
from*Web/Doc_V2_from_Web/07_cleanup_tools/hawkeye-chat-artifacts.zip
from*Web/Doc_V2_from_Web/02_strategy_and_pitch/brochures/_archive_*

# ─── OS / editor cruft ───
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.vscode/
.idea/
*.tmp

# ─── Node / npm (if any docs scripts use it) ───
node_modules/
npm-debug.log
yarn-error.log
package-lock.json

# ─── Env / secrets (paranoia layer) ───
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.key
*.pem
